==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|es|amigo||friend}}, from {{der|en|la|amīcus||friend}}, derived from {{m|la|amo|amāre|to love}}. Compare French {{m|fr|ami}}, Italian {{m|it|amico}}, Portuguese {{m|pt|amigo}} and Romanian {{m|ro|amic}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/əˈmiː.ɡəʊ/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/əˈmiɡoʊ/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{head|en|noun|plural|amigos|feminine|amiga}}

# {{lb|en|informal}} [[friend]]
# {{lb|en|informal|mainly|California}} [[Mexican]]
# {{lb|en|historical}} A [[native]] of the [[Philippines]] who was friendly toward the [[Spanish]].

====Synonyms====
* See also [[Thesaurus:friend]]

====Translations====
