==Old Portuguese==

===Alternative forms===
* {{alter|roa-opt|amig'}}

===Etymology===
From {{inh|roa-opt|la|amīcus||friend; friendly}}, from {{m|la|amō||I love}} + {{m|la|-icus}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/aˈmiɡo/|lang=roa-opt}}

===Noun===
{{head|roa-opt|noun|g=m|plural|amigos|feminine|amiga|feminine plural|amigas}}

# {{l|en|friend}}
#* {{roa-opt-cite-cantigas|E|210|http://www.pbm.com/~lindahl/cantigas/facsimiles/E/383small.gif}}
#*: Mvito foi noſſ'''amigo''' / gabriel quando diſſe / maria deus e tigo.
#*:: Gabriel was our true '''friend''' when he said: "Mary, God is with you".
# {{l|en|lover}}
#* '''13th century''', [[w:Pergaminho Vindel|''Vindel manuscript'']], [[w:Martín Codax|Martín Codax]], [http://cantigas.fcsh.unl.pt/cantiga.asp?cdcant=1308&pv=sim ''Ondas do mar de Vigo''] ([https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/11/Martim_Codax_Cantigas_de_Amigo.jpg facsimile])
#*: Ondas do mar de uigo / ſe uiſtes meu '''amigo'''. / E ay deꝯ ſe uerra cedo.
#*:: Waves of the sea of Vigo / Have you seen my '''lover'''? / Oh God, will he return soon?

